article.description: Reggie Jones scored 24 points and Thomas Wilder added 22 to lift Western Michigan to a 74-67 victory over James Madison on Saturday.
article.headline: Late run lifts Western Michigan over James Madison 74-67
article.linkText: Late run lifts Western Michigan over James Madison 74-67
article.story: KALAMAZOO, Mich. -- Reggie Jones scored 24 points and Thomas Wilder added 22 to lift Western Michigan to a 74-67 victory over James Madison on Saturday. The Broncos (3-6) trailed 57-50 before taking the lead for good with an 18-2 run. WMU led 70-61 when Jackson Kent made a 3-pointer for the Dukes (1-8). After a steal by Yohanny Dalembert, Kent made another 3-pointer to cut the lead to three in the final seconds, but James Madison's Ramone Snowden was called for a foul when WMU tried to inbound the ball again. JMU coach Louis Rowe came out onto the court to complain after that call and received a technical foul. Jones made four free throws to put the game out of reach. Drake LaMont scored 12 points for the Broncos, who made 20 of 26 free throws (76.9 percent). Tom Vodanovich scored 18 points for the Dukes and Kent finished with 16 on 4 of 7 3-pointers.
